            <entry xml:id="entry_arv" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>arv</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>небо</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>sky</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">очень часто говорят</note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">very common is the expression</note>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>wælarv</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>верхнее небо</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>upper sky</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">производные и сложные с %iarv%i: </note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">derivatives and compounds with %iarv%i: </note>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>ærvon</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>небесный</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>heavenly</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>arvnæryn</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>гром</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>thunder</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>arvyrttyvd</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>молния</q>
                            </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („блеск неба“)</note><note
                                type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (“shine of the sky”)</note><abv:tr
                                xml:lang="en">
                                <q>lightning</q>
                            </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („блеск неба“)</note><note
                                type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (“shine of the sky”)</note></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>arvyrdyn</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>радуга</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>rainbow</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>arvy K˳yrdalægonmæ jæ ysxæccæ kæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сведи его (коня) к небесному (кузнецу) Курдалагону</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>take it (horse) to the heavenly (blacksmith) Kyrdalagon</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>70</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>nal wynys arvy cʼæx, nal wynys zæxxy saw</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ты не видишь больше синевы неба, не видишь больше черноты земли</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>you don't see the blue of the sky anymore, you don't see the black of
                                the earth anymore</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Æfx._Xæs."
                            /><biblScope>99</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>arv īw k˳y ferttyvta, wæd īw Tuǧany awydta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>каждый раз, когда сверкало небо (т. е. молния), он видел Тугана</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>every time the sky flashed (i.e. lightning), he saw Tugan</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>99</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>arv næ niccavta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>нас поразило громом (буквально „небо нас поразило“)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>we were struck with thunder (literally “the sky hit us”)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>2</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>i bæx æj rajsta arvæj zænxi astæw</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>конь понес его между небом и землей</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the horse carried him between heaven and earth</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."
                            /><biblScope>28%l10%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mænæj zændǧyndær arvy byn næj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>умнее меня нет под небом</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there is no smarter than me under the sky</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>102</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>arvy ron</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>радуга</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>rainbow</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                    <note type="bibl">(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                                125</biblScope></bibl>)</note>
                </re>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">%iarv%i — закономерная перестановка из %i*avr%i и восходит к
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*abra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wad"/>; однако в других иранских (и индоевропейских) языках
                    слово %iarv%i имеет соответствия со значением не ‘небо’, а ‘облако’, ‘туча’,
                    ‘влага’: <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>awr, aur, haur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>ōrə, owrai</w>
                        <gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>haur</w>
                        <gloss><q>дождь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>abr, awr</w></mentioned> (последнее в диалектах), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>awr(aβr)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>py-aura</w>
                        <gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>ora</w>
                        <gloss><q>Luftraum</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>awra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>дождь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>abhrá-</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ἀφρός</w>
                        <gloss><q>пена</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>amp, amb</w>
                        <gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>. Колебание значений ‘небо’
                    и‘облако’ находим и в других языках, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>небо</w></mentioned> при <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/>
                        <w>nabhas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>туман</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>νέφος</w>
                        <gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>туман</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>sky</w>
                        <gloss><q>небоʼ, первоначально ‘облако</q></gloss></mentioned>. О
                    перемещении значения ‘облако’ → ‘небо’ в связи с климатическими условиями см.:
                            <bibl><author>W. Brandenstein</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">
                            Bemerkungen zum Sinnbezirk des Klimas. Studien zur indogermanischen
                            Grundsprache, 1952, стр. 24—25</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">
                            Bemerkungen zum Sinnbezirk des Klimas. Studien zur indogermanischen
                            Grundsprache, 1952, pp. 24—25</biblScope></bibl>. Общеиранское слово для
                    ‘неба’, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>āsmān-</w></mentioned>, сохранилось, быть может, в <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_az"/> | %ianz%i ‘год’ (см.). С %iarv%i связывают <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_ævraǧ"/> ‘облако’ (см.).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>18, 152,
                            199</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">%iarv%i is a natural methatesis of %i*avr%i and goes back to
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*abra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wad"/>; however, in other Iranian (and Indo-European)
                    languages, the word %iarv%i corresponds not to the meaning ‘sky’ but to ‘cloud’,
                    ‘thundercloud’, ‘moisture’: <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>awr, aur, haur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>ōrə, owrai</w>
                        <gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>haur</w>
                        <gloss><q>rain</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>abr, awr</w></mentioned> (the latter attested in dialects), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>awr(aβr)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>py-aura</w>
                        <gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>ora</w>
                        <gloss><q>Luftraum</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>awra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>rain</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>abhrá-</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ἀφρός</w>
                        <gloss><q>foam</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>amp, amb</w>
                        <gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>. The fluctuation of the meanings
                    ‘sky’ and ʽcloud’ is found in other languages, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>небо</w>
                        <gloss><q>sky</q></gloss></mentioned> along with <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/>
                        <w>nabhas-</w>
                        <gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fog</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>νέφος</w>
                        <gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fog</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>sky</w>
                        <gloss><q>skyʼ, initially ‘cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>. On the semantic
                    shift ʽcloud’ → ‘sky’ due to climatic conditions, see: <bibl><author>W.
                            Brandenstein</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru"> Bemerkungen zum
                            Sinnbezirk des Klimas. Studien zur indogermanischen Grundsprache, 1952,
                            стр. 24—25</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en"> Bemerkungen zum
                            Sinnbezirk des Klimas. Studien zur indogermanischen Grundsprache, 1952,
                            pp. 24—25</biblScope></bibl>. The common Iranian word for ʽskyʼ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>āsmān-</w></mentioned>, was probably preserved in <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_az"/> | %ianz%i ‘year’ (see). %iarv%i is also being
                    associated with <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævraǧ"/> ‘cloud’
                            (see).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                            /><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                            /><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>18, 152, 199</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
